.TH "gnutls_hpke_deinit" 3 "3.8.13" "gnutls" "gnutls"
.SH NAME
gnutls_hpke_deinit \- API function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <gnutls/hpke.h>
.sp
.BI "int gnutls_hpke_deinit(gnutls_hpke_context_t " ctx ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gnutls_hpke_context_t ctx" 12
The HPKE context to deinitialize.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function deinitializes the HPKE context and securely erases any
sensitive information contained within it, such as keys and secrets.
It is important to call this function when the HPKE context is no longer needed
to prevent sensitive data from lingering in memory.
.SH "RETURNS"
0 on success, or a negative error code on failure.
